title: Late nevves out of Barbary In a letter written of late from a merchant there, to a gentl. not long since imployed into that countrie from his Maiestie. Containing some strange particulars, of this new Saintish Kings proceedings: as they haue been very credibly related from such as were eye-witnesses.
author: R. S., fl. 1613.
notes: Two letters, the first signed "R.S.", the second "G.B.".
Editor's foreword signed: I.H., i.e. John Harrison.
Running title reads: Newes from Barbary.
Formerly STC 1377. Identified as STC 1377 on UMI microfilm.
Reproduction of the original in the Folger Shakespeare Library.
